25|$|In {{their role}} as a theatre trope, the Imperial <b>Assault</b> <b>Force</b> are {{preparing}} a stage adaptation of Les Misérables, which Ogami is tasked with directing. The need to properly portray the marriage scene leads to rampant misunderstandings as both Ogami and Imperial <b>Assault</b> <b>Force</b> members think each is proposing to the other. This is further complicated if Ogami had previously romanced {{any member of the}} Imperial and Paris <b>Assault</b> <b>Force.</b> When the Paris <b>Assault</b> <b>Force</b> arrives, if Ogami romanced any of them during the events of Sakura Wars 3, a love triangle situation is created. Ogami must choose which character he wishes to commit to. The production of Les Misérables proves to be a resounding success, and Ogami is left as the sole figure of authority after the Imperial <b>Assault</b> <b>Force's</b> original manager Ikki Yoneda retires, satisfied that Ogami can succeed him. The final scenes vary depending on whether Ogami romanced any member of the Imperial or Paris <b>Assault</b> <b>Force,</b> and which character Ogami chooses to commit to.|$|R
