50|$|In Vietnam Pathfinder Infantrymen were {{inserted}} into areas to establish landing zones for air <b>assaults</b> or other <b>helicopter</b> operations. Pathfinders determined {{the most practical}} landing zones, withdrawal routes, approach lanes, and landing sites for <b>helicopter</b> <b>assaults,</b> in hostile areas. They themselves would then often be extracted with helicopter McGuire rigs.|$|R
